reviews:
10 mins walking from:
- Chatelet Les Halles Metro/RER A/B
- Louvre
- Pompidou

Room are silent and clean.
Wifi is ok.
Good timing of breakfast until 10-30 AM

MINUS: TV channels: only some french channels, small choices.

This was my second time staying at the hotel. Once again, Pedro was extremely welcoming and friendly. I would also like to say that Marta was also extremely lovely throughout my stay. This is honestly my favourite place to stay, so central and perfect for a holiday in Paris. I have already planned to go back in May with my friend.

Good and clean for a 3 star hotel. Close to almost everything as it is in downtown. Could have bathroom slippers, otherwise everything was good.
The only thing that I did not like was Wifi connection. We had room in third floor, connection worked fine through the aile but not in our room.

This was my second stay at this hotel and yet again was a wonderful experience.
Staff are super helpful and friendly and a big shout out for Pedro in reception who was exceptional in his care, helpfulness and hospitality and made me feel well looked after and cared for. Nothing was too much trouble for him.
Location is excellent in the first arrondissement and close to Louvre and easy walking to Opera. Rooms are compact but beautiful design and good use of space. Lighting across the full hotel is beautiful. Sleep qulity was high as the hotel is really quiet.
Breakfast has a selection of hot foods, fresh fruits, cheeses, pastries etc and there is complimentary tea and coffee for the full duration of your stay from the ground floor.
Nice bars and eating places close to the hotel too.
As a female traveller alone I felt very safe at this hotel. Quite the hidden gem

We had a pleasant stay in this lovely hotel with beautiful rooms and good service. the hotel is well located in a quiet street. Only the WIFI in the rooms was lousy which was kind a pity. Service at breakfast was also well.

The position was excellent since I needed to go to the Banque de France, which is literally 2 min walk. However the trim was really small and being on the first floor I could not open the curtain without being seen from the street so I had to have the light on all the time. I am a bit claustrophobic, and I felt a bit of cabin fever

I was excited to experience the unique room but was disappointed by how much it cost compared to the quality and cleanliness. The bed was comfortable but everything else felt worn out. The shower smelled like mold and had mold streaks running from the overhead shower. The person at the front desk apologized and said they were going to fix it but did not offer any sort of discount. The people at the desk were very friendly and helpful otherwise.

Very nice boutique hotel located just a stroll away from Le Louvre and Le Marais. Rooms are nicely furnished and clean. Beds are comfortable. We had two super quiet rooms on the fifth floor overlooking an inside courtyard. Although the rooms are small, there was enough room for the short time you usually spend there when visiting Paris. The setting is indeed clever with room under the bed to store luggage and a cupboard. The staff was kind and helpful. Very good value for price for this 3 star hotel which we found trusts the top of its category.

The receptionist at the evening wasn't very helpful in addressing our queries. We asked for some directions or groceries nearby but he just told us he didn't know. We found the breakfast too expensive as well. I usually book a hotel with breakfast included so I got surprised that it wasn't included during our stay. This may be a mistake on our side but the lady didnt ask us before going inside the dining room. Had we known that we needed to pay for the breakfast, we wouldnt have gotten in. Eur15 per person isn't worth it because there arent many selections.
The room is very small, good thing we stayed for two nights only, more than that will be a bit of a pain.

Incredible design, room spacious enough, clean and staff at the desk helpful, nice and welcoming. I would stay again and again.
Best value for what you get.
Location is a chapter a part: the hotel is at walking distance from the louvre and the main tourist attractions.
Sleeping quality amazing by the way.
In a nutshell, extraordinary!

Small hotel, but offers everything you need. We liked the style of this hotel and can recommend it to people, who want to try something different. You'll find everything you need for a relaxing stay in a very well located area near the city center. Within a 5 minutes walk, you will be at The Louvre.

We also have to definitely highlight Pedro's outstanding hospitality. He has shown us so many good restaurants and given us so many tips to make our stay even more beautiful. The chat with him was always very friendly. Especially the organization for the birthday of my girlfriend was fantastic. He organized everything I asked for in such an easy manner! Congrats, very well!

There was absolutely nothing to dislike about this hotel!! The staff was amazing, courteous, and very very attentive to guests needs =) I've never experienced such great customer service before at a hotel when travelling. The hotel manager, Boris, was by far the best... took the time to find taxis and help me plan fun activities to do during my stay to keep me entertained. I had a minor issue in my room (I couldn't figure out the A/C), and he did not hesitate to come up and help me resolve it😊😊 Also props to Pedro at reception who was very friendly and helpful when I needed a bandaid. If you go to Paris, Hotel Odyssey is where you need to stay👍🏾❤

Very good price for value. We went last weekend and spend 1 night. The staff is very helpful and friendly, the hotel is small but clean, well located and has a comfortable bed. It’s also quiet so highly recommended !!!

This hotel is narrow and straight up. It is situated in the middle of the block on Rue Herold and the hotel section is about 15 feet across! There is an elevator, and air-conditioning which in August was a must! The room is basically the size of the bed, I kid you not! The bathroom has a glass wall into the bedroom.
If you stay here it is because of the price and the location. It is very close to the Louvre, and we walked to Orsay, Orangarie, Rodin, the Eiffel Tower, Rue Cler, the National Museum. They offer a breakfast spread for 12 Euro if you eat there more than 3 days. Staff was very helpful with cabs and getting around.

Very nice hotel, near the metro station Les Halles - Châtelet. A lot of restaurants and bars are near to the hotel. Everything was very clean and breakfast was fine as well. Mattresses should be replaced though.

Don't go with any expectations - Expensive hotel with respect to facilities available. Location is good as very near to Louvre Museum. Many Restaurants nearby.Breakfast is very basic.Carry your own Toothbrush/Shaving Kit as nothing is available in room

Everything is perfect and impeccable. The room size is satisfied with awesome modern decoration. Absolutely a comfortable place for accommodation and also in a good location. All the staff is nice and helpful.

Room was very small but modern and clean. Pillows were the only problem as they were flat and too firm. Front desk lady spoke English and was helpful. I would recommend this hotel to others. We didn't have the €15 breakfast so I can't comment on that.

The hotel located in the historical centre very close to Louvre and has great public transport connection to the rest of the city. The staff is very welcoming and helpful, the 24-hour reception is convinient for late arrivals and early check outs. The room is small but comfortable and clean. The reception area and the breakfast room has a great modern atmosphere, the breakfast offered a great selection. The reception staff was very helpful even in some unexpected circumstances, always ready to help.

We booked this hotel for a weekend away, attracted by its central location and excellent rates. We weren't disappointed! The staff were friendly and helpful (particularly when my partner required some medical attention), and we had a really pleasant stay.

I was a bit worried about the size of the rooms after reading some of the TripAdvisor reviews from other guests, particularly as my partner and I are quite tall (he's 6'5) but our CocOon room (the smallest one on offer) was perfect for us. We had plenty of space to move around and relax, and took advantage of the under-bed storage to stash our suitcases out of view.

The hotel is located on a quiet street anyway, but we heard no noise at all from our room (no. 15, on the first floor with window facing onto a small inner courtyard). It was unseasonably warm during our stay, but luckily the room had great air conditioning (really quiet too!) and it was easy to set the temperature to our preferences.

We only took breakfast in the hotel on one morning of our trip as there are lots of tempting cafes and restaurants in the area, but we did enjoy the meal in the hotel and found it very convenient when we wanted to make the most of our sunny Sunday morning. It turns out that we wake up earlier than most of Paris at the weekend!

We're already talking about using this hotel for our next trip to Paris.

Was very disappointed on arrival the rooms look nothing like the website and that was the whole reason we booked this hotel because the rooms looked modern and different. Your better off staying at a premier in because that’s basically what this was. Very misleading pictures from there website.

Very decent location in Les Halles, if the particular street is a little desolate. Rooms are tiny, but who cares? Staff were friendly, with varying degrees of proficiency in English. Breakfast was pretty good. I’d stay there again...

3* is generous. Nothing particularly nice about this hotel, wouldn’t stay here again. The hotel itself looks like a nightclub, with dark halls and coloured lights. The room is very small but modern, unclean with stains on the carpets. Thin walls, made us hear everything going on in the hall. The TV wasn’t a smart tv like it said - or it didn’t work, all channels spoke french with no subtitles. Didn’t feel especially safe in this hotel, not sure why just a vibe - maybe it’s because the window opens out to a small patio that all the other rooms share so they had access to our window. However, very good powerful shower and large comfortable bed, good service at the reception.

Small basic rooms but comfortable and clean. Good location.
Rooms got stuffy overnight and air con didn’t work. Fine for a short stay but would recommend somewhere else for a longer stay due to size.
Staff friendly.
Couple of good restaurants nearby

Very good service! Hotel room & toilet were small but what can you expect in Paris. :) Rooms were facing inner yard so it was not loud despite central location.

Toilet reminded me of my student accommodation in Germany, it was a plastic box basically, but nothing wrong with that!

(A side note: Why do hotels still use soap bars? That’s pretty eco-unfriendly. Would it be best just to install soap dispensers that you can fill with liquid soap, and thereby avoid throwing away half used bars.)

Modern, new, neat yet usage is visible. Unusual theme of a spaceship like. Adam in the reception is very kind, polite and helpful, actually they all are. It's not fancy, fits well for young/adventurous and open minded people that don't ger bothered of tiny places. We are in Paris so what do you expect anyway, but yes this here, really will cramp you inn yet then again for me it's not a problem ☺️.

After looking for different options of hotels and apartments for rent, I decided to choose this place.

Located a few minutes walking distance from the train station Châtelet Les Halles that comes from the Charles de Gaulle airport and only three blocks from the Musée du Louvre. Around the area there are many restaurants with different specialties and some bars with interesting cocktails.

The staff was always friendly and helpful, and I had no problem with the language barrier (they speak English). The rooms are certainly quite small, but if your travel plan is to be away from the hotel exploring and touring the city, this place is definitely all you need to rest and bathe.

Great location, nice hotel, great buffet, clean, quiet place. Single room is small, but has everything needed. Only problem was with TV channels - NO English channels, only French :-) Hotel staff was very friendly.

Really interesting interior design. Very friendly and helpful staff . The room is quite small but has everything you need. Very clean.It has a very good air conditioning system which is so quiet that you can sleep with it on all night. Very quiet location for a good night's sleep. Great location for exploring tourist traps. We did not take breakfast because it was steep at 14€ per head -instead we walked round the corner and ate at a cafe for 15€ for two.
I would definitely use again when visiting the centre of Paris.
Parking outside the hotel is very limited.

Great location, value, comfort, cleanliness and professional staff. This is not my first stay and would highly recommend. If yo require spacious rooms (like those found in the US), you may need to think twice, but if you're familiar with the smaller European room size, this one checks all the boxes. I've stayed here before and will stay again.

Great location, and very quiet. Comfortable bed. Very ‘trendy’ vibe but not necessarily in a good way....kind of strange colors and decor. My room was tiny and the hallway very narrow. Staff was mixed friendliness; didn’t realize until checkout there was a breakfast room behind the curtain (with a paid breakfast) as I was not informed at check-in.

Greetings,

Spent 10 days in paris last April to visit some family members.

We chose this hotel for it's proximity to everything and for it's location being on a quiet street so that we could get decent sleep quality.

Those expectations were met fully.

The hotel is super well located - 2e arr - walking distance from chatelet les halles main travel hub (subway, rer, etc..). - use the saint - eustache exit to walk to the hotel. Chatelet les halles is a quite large station, so you can easily get lost..

The hotel is located on a small and quiet street - herold -. It's a small boutique hotel and it is really super modern design (think japanese design).

we had the most 'roomy' one - galileo - and despite being the roomiest it is still quite cramped - so heads-up to my fellow north american travellers - make sure you bring minimal luggage.

We had a room on 4th floor, totally quiet, no street noise at all, sleep quality guaranteed.

The room is really modern design, the bed is in some sort of little 'alcove' - can be challenging to get to the bed and out if you have a bad back..the bed was really comfortable, if you are claustrophobic, you may have a weird feeling sleeping in the 'alcove' but we were OK. Just a bit of advice.

The shower is top quality - probably the best shower equipment i've seen in an hotel.

The restroom is separate from the shower.

This is really for intimate couple, you see the person in the shower from where-ever you are in the room, so..be aware.

We had a small - really small - storage area and a mini-fridge.

Hotel supplies a cell phone that you can use for free to make local calls, use internet, etc.. (but you won't be able to receive calls) - convenient tough to keep with us when you wander around in the city.

The price tag is a bit steep - but you are in paris, not much bargain there.

The breakfast area downstairs is quite nice, but the breakfast itself is quite expensive so we skipped that and got our own stuff to convenience store (plenty around) or go to the nearby cafe (le moulin de la vierge, 5 minutes walk) for breakfast.

The hotel location is ideal, 10-15 minutes walk from louvres, 20 minutes from la seine, 30 minutes from notre dame etc..in 10 days we never even took the subway, we just walked everywhere throughout the city as this is a real treat in itself - walk in this awesome city.

We would go back there at our next visit to paris.

/Montrealer2

This hotel is a short walk from the museums and has a very friendly and helpful staff. The rooms each have a cell phone you can use on your outings to navigate the city and also to make calls back to the states, all free of any extra charge. The rooms were small (which we knew going in) yet clean. They do offer a breakfast at an extra charge which we did not find worth the price, but there are good cafes nearby.

I originally planned to stay in paris for only 4 days, but do to a transit strike my stay was extended by 2 days. The staff here were extremely accommodating. They helped me extend my trip, showed me how to get to all the places in Paris. In Particular one staff member Yanis was extremely helpful with me extending my stay, he was incredibly friendly and kind, he was one cool dude. The whole staff was amazing, and the rooms were fabulous, I would highly recommend this hotel to anyone who is planning to stay in Paris. Also the location is central to about all of the coolest spots to see in Paris.

Very nice design, in the city center a perfect place to stay for one or two nights maybe not more because the hotel is pretty dark and the room are not too big, but in the complex is clean and the staff polite so I would recommend it for business travellers. I really enjoyed the green colour of the bar and the room. Fur sure I'll come back.

We enjoyed the good location, the design atmosphere and the kind staff. The room was very cosy and the bed was better than average! The staff helped us out with dinner hints and some insider tips about leisure activities in the city. We are very happy customers and will certainly come back when we need a sleepover in Paris!

A very comfortable and modern hotel in a lively, bustling area, close the the Tuileries Gardens, the Palais Royal, and the Louvre museum. The rooms are small but if you're looking for the best location, the best price, and mostly to only use your room to sleep, don't look any further, this is the hidden gem you were looking for.

The design in this hotel is amazing, the rooms are small, it's perfect for exploring the city,
The shower was good, sleep quality good, the in-room technology was fabulous, good fast free wi-fi, my only concern was just a small room.
The breakfast buffet option was excellent.
Good for business if you are a solo traveller.
For leisure perfect for couples, a great chance to get very close!

very modern, awesome friendly helpful staff, this place is great! the rooms are very cool looking into a courtyard in the center of the building so no view but, its like staying in a spaceship with all the lights and controls on the headboard and Samsung smart phones in every room. I loved the design.
the location is great walking anywhere is easy and again the STAFF IS AWESOME

Awesome location, friendly/helpful staff that speak English, great lighting in the room. The room was unique and cool however, the limited space did become annoying when trying to get ready with 2 people. The bed was comfortable.

We stayed at Hotel Odyssey for two nights. We arrived early on the first day and were able to check in and leave our bags at the hotel to explore Paris while our room was prepared. When we got back our room was ready.

As other reviews have stated, the room itself is on the smaller side (although we’ve stayed in smaller in central London!). This wasn’t an issue for us as we spent most of our time out exploring the city. The toilet was the snuggest of everything in the room - hardly any space to stand up! It is basic (no bath robes, no toiletries, no complimentary drinks, etc...) but on the whole the room was good value for money. Bed was comfy, room was quiet, location of the hotel was perfect. We had breakfast included and it was great. A whole range of items to choose from - highly recommend it.

The staff were superb. Really helpful and polite. When checking out, again we didn’t have a train home until early evening so asked to leave our bags at the hotel. This was no trouble for the staff. We left our bags all day while we explored more of the fantastic city and collected just before we had to make our way back to the train station.

We stayed there for 3 nights. The hotel is very well located. Very close to the Louvre.
The bedroom is very very small.
It was very clean at the first day.
On the second day, we left the “please clean the bedroom” note at the door, and when we can back very late that day, someone had turned the note to “don’t disturb” and the room was still a mess. That is the reason I will not rate it better.
If you are traveling with a friend, I recommend you to book different rooms, unless you don’t mind seeing each other taking a shower or going for number 2.
You have no private at all in the bathroom.
People at the reception are very nice.
I would stay there again if the cleaning issue hadn’t happened.

If you are like me that, particular for business where you need to be coat conscious yet a central location, this is the place for you. No frills - no shampoo cap (who needs it) or tooth paste but a folding desk, shower, toilet, hair drier etc are all there. The bed was big and comfortable. It is not 4/5 stars maybe, but staff are very helpful and I sat in the breakfast room/bar until 23:00 last night working. ‘Room is for sleeping’, the receptionist said. He is absolutely right. My room was one of orange rooms. It was a little plasticky, but as I said, the best was comfortable, the reception has adapters. So I have nothing to complain. I will probably go back there again.

Hotel Odyssey is in a great location, only a short walk to the metro, Louvre, and Notre Dame. The staff is very friendly and will always say hi when you walk in or leave and are accommodating if you need anything. We stayed in the Orange Room.

Pros
- Great location in 1st Arr. near the Louvre, and many restaurants/cafes
- Friendly staff
- Hot shower with high water pressure
- Plenty of plugs and charging outlets including USB outlets.
- Large comfy bed
- Inexpensive

Cons
- Room was a little dirty with stains on the carpet
- No screen on the window so you can't keep it open at night
- A/C is turned off Oct 1st and there are still warm days in Oct
- Light buttons on the bed are confusing

The main problem for me was the hotel turns off their air conditioning at the beginning of October even though there are still some pretty warm days left in the year. Also, there are no screens on the windows so you can't really keep the windows open at night to let the cool air in. There were a few other issues with some areas being dirty or stained, and we had trouble figuring out the light buttons, but we liked our time here and would stay here again.

A wonderful hotel. On my top list in Paris

The pros:
Very friendly staff, beautifully designed room, very centrally located, in a neighbourhood with a lot of character, breakfast is lovely, rooms are quiet and bright.

Cons:
In winter the rooms can get cold at night as they take control of the heating centrally in the evening. I am assuming that the reverse must happen in summer.
The rooms are small. Regardless of the type, they are not ideal for a couple.

The staff in the hotel are nice and the location is perfect but the hotel is not as new as you may think it is ....
The carpet floor, "couch" and in general it is very dirty..
I don't know if they put a smell in the aircondition, but this smell was very strong and it did not go away!
the elevator is very scary...
I came during FW and my small room with small window (not even a window towards the street) I have paid 265 EUR!!!!!!!!! definetly too expensive!!!

Friendly staff
Cool design
Small rooms but perfect for Paris as you're out all the time.
Cool white bathrooms
I really liked this hotel and the staff were friendly and chatty.
Location is superb - you just can't get more central
Great value for money !

Great location, good price and lovely staff.
will definitely come back.

Room is slightly small but really lovely and efficient
Breakfast slightly expensive.

Staff is very welcoming and helpful.

Really good location

I booked this trip as a surprise for my sister's birthday. Having looked at many reviews on hotels decided on this one. We were both very happy on arrival. Did take us a few minutes to figure out where it was from the train station but got directions and found it down a quiet back street.
We was greeted at reception by a young lady and told we was a bit early for check in but could leave our bags and go explore which was perfect. When we arrived back later we checked in and got allocated our room. We got a double room. The reception area is very nicely decorated and quirky.
The lift was on the small side with luggage but we both fit in. Again the corridors to the room were narrow and dark but it all added to the hotels charm for us.
We got to our room which had a double bed shower toilet area which is all we really need. Yes it's on the small side but was clean and comfortable. There was plenty of plug sockets to charge our devices we is always a plus. We was also provided with a hotel mobile phone that we could take out with us if we chose to. We really enjoyed our stay and the hotel helped make my sister's birthday special. The facilities down stairs were also very clean. We checked out on our final day and left our luggage again in storage so we could go out and enjoy our final day. Thank you all we had a great time in Paris.

Great Location ! very close to the Louvre
also the metro is few meters away
Great Concept & Design , I got a pink room , little bit small but lovely
Clean and Fresh Rooms , and the staff is extremely helpful
The breakfast was nice , but not too exciting

We stayed at the Hotel Odyssey the first week of August. I had been warned about small Paris hotel rooms once you move away from the typical franchise hotel brands. The pictures from their website intrigued me, and I wasn't let down once I got there. From the short distance from the Paris Nord train station to its location, this Hotel has everything going for it. It is located on a small, quiet side street that gives you that Paris feel. It is newly renovated in a very contemporary style and uses the space it has in a very efficient way. The lobby is clean and check-in was quick and easy, with front desk clerks who spoke English. The room was very modern and clean and their use of the space they had to work with is to be commended. Everything in the room was first class. They even provided Samsung cell phones that gave you free unlimited North America calling and texting and provided a series of helpful tourist based apps!! Although I did not use the restaurant, it looked very intimate and provided breakfast and dinner. I highly recommend this hotel if you are looking for the true Paris experience.

This hotel was great, but it definitely has a love hotel vibe. We paid extra for the biggest room, but the shower is still visible from the bed... which is incredibly sexy for couples, but I can imagine it might be a bit awkward for others.

The cocoon bed was amazing. I want one in my home.

Great location next some delicious restaurants. 15 minute walk to the Louvre and 25 minute walk to the Eiffel Tower. Only stayed for one night but the staff were awesome and very willing to accommodate anything we needed.

Great location. Friendly, helpful staff. Quirky and different room layout. 3 stars - quiet and clean.

Rooms are small - stayed in the largest and it was still 'cosy'. Very different layout - cocoon style bedroom looks great but in practice no so much. Need to be a gymnast to get in and out of the bed - not great if you have to get up in the middle of the night, in the dark and not disturb your partner! I can confirm it's not do-able! I also wonder how they manage to make the bed up each day - whoever does it needs a raise as it won't be an easy task! Also lighting layout is confusing and difficult to grasp.

Bathroom is open plan too which may not suit everyone. Despite being newly refurbished there is some early signs of wear and tear in this area. Room is probably more suited for a leisure stay rather than business use as there is limited desk space. There is also very limited storage and none at all for your luggage so it shares the limited room space with you.

Breakfast available but it's not included in room rate - there are lots of nice restaurants in the immediate vicinity. Metro options are good - choice of stations each about a 10 min walk away.

Did have a couple gripes- it's a double room yet only one bathrobe supplied. Why?

Also, a very limited mini bar (water, soft drinks and beer) was provided free ...but on the first night only. Don't understand this concept given room price is the same each night.

Be aware there is a separate tourist tax applied when departing the hotel - this worked out just over €6 total for two nights. Not much but it's an inconvenience.

The hotel is ok for short stays. The location is excellent, a bit more than 5 min walk from Chatelet Les Halles, where the train from the airport stops. My room, on the fifth floor, purple themed, was very small, it felt a bit claustrophobic. Breakfast was very good. The staff are very helpful

My husband, daughter and I stayed at Hotel Odyssey for 4 nights. We originally had (2) of the smaller rooms but my husband and I upgraded to the larger room for our last few nights.

The Cocoon room is great for singles. My husband and I barely fit in it, however; the room is super cute and functional.

I didn't eat breakfast at the hotel but I did look at it. It looked good but I wanted to eat out in one of the multiple nearby cafes.

The location is amazing!!! We wanted to stay near the Lourve and Notre Dame and both were in walking distance. It is just a short uber ride to anywhere else you want to go.

The reason for the 5 stars (besides the location) was the staff! They were very nice, spoke perfect English and always available to help us or answer any question. They even went so far.... my husband left his blazer in our room and he needed it for an event about 4 hours away, the day after we checked out. They overnighted the blazer to us... not a problem.

I would definately recommend staying there!

This is a wonderful little modern hotel that I really couldn't fault during a recent stay with my partner.
We stayed in a Odyssey room with an orange theme. It was small but it's what you expect in Paris. (Going off this size, I'd imagine the smaller Cocoon rooms too be a bit too small. If you can, definitely pay the little extra for a bigger room). We had windows that opened out onto the street, which were a little noisy in the morning with traffic (despite it being a back street) but it didn't really bother us too much as we were up early to explore the city. The room had a flat screen smart tv, but none of the 'smart services' worked (seems a bit strange to not offer the service if the tv allows it). Not a massive issue but maybe something for the hotel to consider for the future?
The shower was amazing and I liked the whole open plan to the room with the shower being right next to the bed - however this may be an issue for some guests who are staying with someone they don't wish to see in the shower! The toilet dos have a private sliding door though.
One thing that we found extremely helpful was the smartphone to use during your stay. It was great for using around the city and finding good restaurants to eat at during our stay. Fantastic and more hotels should consider offering a similar services.
We didn't eat breakfast at the hotel, so cannot comment on that. There were lots of cafes nearby so we opted to dine out each morning.
The location of the hotel is great, just a short walk from Châtelet-Les Halle station and the Louvre.
Overall a great hotel, would definitely recommend and would stay there again.

We have been for only one night.
I have to say there are some good point: the location is very convenient, and the hotel is brand new, with a lot of details and good originality in the design. To have a decently sized room you need to go at least to the second category though, which raises the price. No fridge existing.
I would say that is a bit too expensive though,and also the breakfast is too much expensive (16 euros) for what it offers, even if it is good.
The service is ok, but not particularly warm.

It is the second time I stay in this hotel. Staff is friendly as always. Breakfast choice is abundant and good quality, I like the eggs and salad which you can feel the freshness, different from those smelling like days old buffet.

The hotel is attentive to send me a pre-check-in survey to note my preference. I prefer any colours but the red tone, the hotel is very nice to accommodate my needs.

I will definitely stay again in this hotel, location is super convenient, less than 10 minutes walk from Chatelet Les Halles, hub of many metro RER line.

Thank you to the staff team!

Great location and staff. Abundant late night eats around the hotel and the staff was superb. Very clean hotel but smaller than expected, not enough room to lay or hang clothes so we lived out of our suitcase; convenience of location makes up for all pitfalls.

Our experience - We were met by very friendly front desk staff and had an easy enough time checking in and out. The room itself was very clean and interesting with the shower having a glass wall looking into the room. Luckily I was here with my fiance and not a family member, but other than that it was pretty cool. The headboard of the bed has a control pad for the lights of the room, which was really nice when going to bed or waking up (although I'm not sure all buttons worked). I also enjoyed the color scheme (each room has a different color of the rainbow), as we had the Red room and that happens to be my favorite color. Unfortunately, the hotel did not offer free coffee, but there was an abundance of restaurants in the vicinity in which to find some.

The Odyssey Hotel is close to the heart of Paris (near to Louvre, Opera, les Halles) and in a quiet street, so has the benefits of being a refuge from the noise of the city. In its stylish way it uses the small space it occupies with great effect. The rooms are pretty tiny, however, one does not feel this. Mirrors and glass walls create a "Tardis" effect, which make it surprisingly comfortable. The staff are pleasant, the beds comfortable and the shower brilliant. Only three warnings to potential customers: watch out for walking into the mirrors at night (when a bit disorientated!), there is no door to the washing area, so going to the toilet is a little public, and if you do not like being watched while showering, the glass wall between you and the bed might be off-putting. Otherwise, highly recommended.

The Hotel Odyssey was a fantastic place to stay. The location is great. The room was tiny, but the decor and atmosphere were so fun we didn't mind. We didn't do much besides sleep there anyways. The breakfast was delicious and plentiful with crepes, eggs, ham, fruit, yogurt, pain au chocolate, nutella, baguettes, etc. The best ammenity was the cell phone provided with the room that we could take with us during our stay. It was invaluable! We would have been so lost without it since our US phones didn't work in Paris. We will definitely return to this hotel if we come to Paris again.

Loved this hotel. Rooms are small but brilliantly designed, and far better than many larger rooms in other hotels. I travelled solo, but imagine that if you are a couple and want to hang around in your room you might find it claustrophobic.

Staff and location are great. A fantastic find. I hope to be back soon.

Great location, very quiet room. Checking in, the room had such an overpowering smell of air freshener that it got us ill. Management found us a better smelling room with an upgrade. The room design is oddball: like the set of Clockwork Orange, but it was interesting and fun. Very nice people on staff.

The room was vey simple and small but very clean, which I appreciated a lot. We booked the room with breakfast buffet for convenience, but the breakfast was kind of disappointing compared to the price we payed. The breakfast buffet consisted of the very basic food like bread, cereals, fruit, cheese, juice, coffee etc. Only the bread looked fresh, all other ingredients looked and tasted like they have been sitting out for a long time even though we were among the first eaters in the mornings. It was clear that money was trying to be saved on the buffet. I would recommend the hotel for the location, the clean room and the friendly staff but would recommend to eat the breakfast out as you can probably get a great fresh breakfast with the similar amount of money from the bakeries located close by.

Nice hotel, great location!
Take advantage of it while planning your tour around the city.
Design reminds of a spaceship and the rooms are organised efficiently. Bathrooms are clean and rain shower is super. Big and comfortable bed, nooked in the space.
Some say rooms are small, but I never understand this kind of comment. They offer enough space for their purpose, rest or sleep when needed, change, use the bathroom... it is an hotel, right?
Think about this hotel when you go to Paris.

Our family stayed in the hotel during a whirlwind weekend trip to Paris, and we were fortunate to have found Hotel Odyssey! Edgy and modern decor, the kids stayed in their own room, as the rooms were a bit small which is common in the core of the City. We all enjoyed the service, room quality, and most of all the location. A direct train (RER-B) from CDG got us to a metro station only a 5 minute walk from the hotel. And the Louvre, Notre Dame, and other attractions were very close, not to mention great restaurants and cafes.

My fiancee and I stayed here for three nights and enjoyed the convenience to the train & Louvre. It's a "modern" hotel vibe with clean rooms and a very helpful staff! Great area and a short walk away from great restaurants!

We stayed here for 4 nights at the beginning of March 2017.
The location: Could not be better. Not more than a 10 minute walk from Forum des Halles, which is a huge shopping mall and has everything you could ever need including many restaurants and access to the RER and metro which has a direct line to Charles de Gaulle airport. The hotel itself is on a very quiet sidestreet and we never heard any noise from outside whilst we were there. There are many restaurants and cafes within a few minutes walk and we were spoilt for choice.

The hotel: We stayed in the cocoon room and after reading a few reviews on here before we went we were worried the room was going to be tiny. We were pleasantly surprised and had enough room for our needs. It is compact but perfect to just use as a base for sightseeing and being out and about for most of the day. The room was very clean, one of the cleanest we have stayed in and were given fresh towels each day. The bed was extremely comfy. We decided not to have the breakfast as there are plenty of places to eat close by. Each room is provided with a mobile phone which we took out with us every day. It gave information about places to visit and eat which could be booked through the phone. We found the phone invaluable as it gave us directions when we lost our bearings a few times.

The staff: Were very friendly and helpful and available 24/7 if we ever needed anything. When we arrived we were provided with a map and also suggestions of where to eat.

We had a great stay in this hotel and would definitely recommend it. If we were to visit Paris again in the future we would certainly return.

We were staying in Hotel Odyssey in December for 5 nights. And it was amazing!
First of all, hotel's location is perfect. It is not more than in 10 minutes walk from a big transport hub Châtelet – Les Halles. So you can get to everywhere very fast. But a lot of attractions you can reach by foot! Louvre is in 10 minutes, Centre Pompidou is in 15 minutes.
Staff in hotel was also great! Special thanks for night receptionists (the only ones we met) for being polite and helpful! Room was cleaned every day. It was small, but we knew about it and it's normal for Paris.
Next time, when we visit Paris, we will stay here for sure, and will recommend it to our friends.

My girlfriend and I booked this stay a couple weeks ago and couldn't be happier. Everyone at the hotel was super-friendly and the location was perfect! Close to all of the major sights in Paris and walking distance to great restaurants. We would highly recommend!

If you like good design, space age, minimalism, colours than the Odysssey Hotel is right for you. The rooms are small (12m) and you feel like in a cocoon. It is perfectly located in the centre of Paris, in a calm street with few cars at night. I found the breakfast a bit expensive 16€ and there is a sign that Cappuccino and other coffees cost even extra which I found a bit exagerated. OTher than that the Hotel is perfect for a nice stay in Paris.

We had a great time, in a great hotel, in a great city. Loved the hotel and will be back. Clean rooms, friendly staff, central location. Can recommend to everyone! We stayed with family for a city trip, everything iswalking distance.

The location is perfect, very close to many attractions. Also i had a nice staying in the hotel, the staffs here are very friendly. This hotel is cosy and lovely, the breakfast is good too! Quiet and safe area. Highly recommend

Accommodation; the room I received was on the top floor, after opting for a larger room. The room was on the smaller size however not too small. On entry you come straight into the bedroom. A large double bed with a small chair. The bathroom is compact but spacious with a shower room and a separate toilet room.

Facilities; there are very few facilities at this hotel. There is a bar room that doubles as a breakfast room. Breakfast was expensive at €20+ and I did not take up the offer as there are plenty of restaurants in the area.

Service; good service though out. Good english, efficient and friendly.

Location; great location. Surrounded by restaurants and bars and only a 10 minute walk from a large shopping centre. Only a 5 - 15 minute walk to most tourist attractions.

Recommendation; It might be a 3 start hotel but its a 4 star standard. Quirky, simple but very clean and located exactly were you need to be.

Just arrived in grand Paris with my husband and our baby girl who has just turned one, after a two hour quick journey on the Euro star which was effortless and quick.

Having travelled quiet a lot as a couple its amazing what your able to do with a one year old who wants to walk the Paris sidewalks.

Arrived as a birthday treat for my husband for three nights, at the Hotel Odyssey on Rue Harold.

Amazing venue so central, really accommodating to our needs, provided us with a travel cot even though the rooms were small we made the most of it.

We were literally out all morning and afternoon taking in so many sights that the room was our least priority.

The staff at the hotel were so friendly and were so happy to help us warm bottles each morning and night (Thank you so much).

The staff were ever so helpful and a huge help enabling us to enjoy the city with their knowledge.

We did struggle in restaurants slightly with the lack of high chairs, but never put us off we just used the pushchair, there are lots of little parks close by where our daughter could have a lovely walk and play along the route to some of the top sightseeing attractions like the Louvre and the Eiffel Tower.

We decided that as a family we would like to see Paris on foot and walked to the Eiffel Tower which was just over an hours walk but really worth the visit. Was not as crowded as i had visioned either.
We also walked to Notre Dame, The Moulouin Rouge and the Louvre.
The streets are narrow but was fine with our pushchair.

The Louvre was fantastic for the pram and the lifts were always empty, the changing facilities were basic but all you would need which is hard to find in the city.

Never saw many babies or children in the restaurants while we were eating out but was just an observation now i have a child of my own.

This was a totally different break due to us having a baby to add to our adventures but absolutely loved every part if being able to share, a new way of travelling and being able to manage and still be able to enjoy a city break and adapt.

Everyone was so friendly and pleasant everywhere we went.

So many fantastic places to eat we decided that we would grab breakfast in the go each morning out of the hotel only due to being able to time thing's right around our baby.

There are loads of deli's and sandwich shops in your doorstep and loads of supermarkets that sell everything you would possibly need.

The hotel was lovely and clean and our room was lovely, all that we needed and one excellent shower also a hand held one so i was able to shower our baby girl each morning.

Loved every part of our stay in Paris and can not wait to come back and hit the shops for a shopping weekend as the shopping here is fantastic one of the best i have seen.

I have to say for someone who loves shopping you would not get bored here you have designer to high street to markets all with an easy reach it's superb

Love you Paris can not wait to return
Avoir from the Whites

This is a smaller hotel with absolutely no negative points.

Great location, friendly staff, simple well laid out small room, clean, super comfortable bed, fast wifi. It's got everything.

Note that the basic room really is just a bed and bathroom - no desk and you would be hard pressed to even open a suitcase without putting it on the bed first.

But so long as the location works for you, and you only need a bed and nothing else, this is a perfect solution. Huge bang for your buck.

Positive:
We were greeted with pleasant attendance where we checked in much earlier, which was very helpful in terms of our plans during the day.
Our room was very clean and was cleaned at the same level every day. Very pleased with the cleanliness of the rooms. The room had a safe which was very reassuring. The hotel is quite centrally located and is close to public transportation, as well as restaurants and clothing stores. The area is safe and cozy.
We got to know a receptionist, Amar, who was very nice and helpful. He did everything possible to satisfy his clients. Professional and great service from him 🙂

Negative:
Small rooms. Lack of kettle, coffee and cups. It would have been nice to have something similar in the rooms. Last day before we were returning back home the receptionist (a young woman) forgot to repay deposit (which was 50 euros) and bill us for our drinks. It all ended with that I was called by the same receptionist where I had to pay over the phone. Poor service from "that" receptionist.

In the end: I could recommend this hotell.

I absolutely loved this hotel! It was my first time in Paris, so I took to Trip Advisor for a recommendation and I'm so glad I did. This was a fantastic location with the friendliest concierge! Seriously, ask them for anything and they can help you with it. We were able to purchase museum passes and hop on hop off bus tours right then and there which was so convenient. There is also free WiFi and AC/heating.

It was about a five minute walk to the Lourve and about a 13 minute walk from the Opera House. The hotel is on a quiet street but turn the corner and there are a bunch of restaurants and shops to peruse. For amazing pastries, make sure you go to Moulin de la Vierge. It's a two minute walk away and it's HEAVEN.

The room itself is small, which is to be expected, but they make the most of the space. Each floor is associated with a color and we had a nice hunter green room. The room was always clean and had a safe. There is no fridge, but they will include a carafe of water which you can ask to be refilled at the front desk. They also have a nice breakfast, which if you buy in advanced is 11 Euros/person instead of the 16 Euros when you pay there. It's pretty good with a selection on cheeses, meats, breads, croissants, eggs, and fruit. Think of it as a more sophisticated and elevated continental breakfast. It also has an espresso machine and a variety of juices available. Also included in the room is an Android phone that is free for you to use. It has unlimited 4g internet and unlimited calling within the EU, Canada, and USA which I never fully understood how to navigate but still available all the same.

If you're looking for an affordable place to stay in Paris, then this is it! I would say this hotel would be better suited for couples rather than families since it would be way too cramped with more than 2 people/room. Highly, highly recommend! Merci beaucoup to Paul and Marie for all their help!!

Everything was nice. Reception and everything was excellent. Just one mention, the room i stayed (room 14) didn't automatically close the door. After a long time while i was left i found the door opened. Nothing was missing but just wanted to let you know

Friendly helpful staff. Great location, close to the metro and only a 10 minute walk from the louvre. Restaurants and plenty of places to eat nearby. Rooms very clean and get cleaned on a daily basis. Shops nearby but they only stay open till 10pm. Clean rooms. 10/10 service.

The stay was amazing and you can't beat the location! It's only a couple blocks from the Lourve and there's plenty of restaurants and shops nearby. I stayed in the Cocoon, which is small, but for two people it's perfect, since we're only in there to sleep and the rest of time in the town. You won't be disappointed with the stay and it was super clean as well. I didn't have breakfast there, but it available for an extra charge.

Very clean hotel with helpful and friendly staff. Perfect for a person travelling alone for business - location is also excellent for exploring Paris, particularly the Louvre. Would say that the rooms are a little quirky - quite modern, so don't book if you prefer things more traditional! Only thing I would have liked was tea and coffee making facilities in the room

We loved it here. My fiancé and I were so grateful for the lovely staff. They were available at all times and keen to help were required. We walked in on a few of occasions with the bottle of wine and they were quick to offer glasses and corkscrew for us to enjoy. They helped with recommendations for places to eat and they printed all our tickets for tours ect as we required them.
The rooms were unique, adequately sized and fun. Everything was cleaned to a high standard and felt very comfortable.
Location wise, the Louve is literally around the corner. Plenty to see and do on foot from here!
Would go back every time we're in Paris!

We had a great stay at the Hotel Odyssey. The location was convenient - only about a 7-10-minute walk away from the Metro/RER station and the bus stops. The receptionists were wonderful. Upon our arrival, they provided us with maps and highlighted points of interest and provided restaurant recommendations. Despite being small, the room was clean. We appreciated having an elevator in the hotel, as well as 24-hour assistance at the reception desk. You can request a room color ahead of time.

If you are arriving by RER, I'd suggest using the St. Eustache exit from the Chatelet Les Halles RER station, as that exit is closest to the hotel.

The room in the hotel is clean and nice, but very tiny. In the shower is cold cause of the fan I guess, which we couldn't turn off. The room service was very bad, they didn't refreshed our water, even though we asked them to do so, they've done it only once. I wouldn't recommend the breakfast, I didn't like it. And the view from the room was ugly. But they offered us the free city tax, because we didn't like the service and that's the only reason I've rated it 4 instead of 3. Oh, and they also give a free phone with 4g connection, which is very convenient.

Bed is perfect
Location is perfect. Very clean and the stuff is helpfull and friendly. The wc was a bit small though but the general picture is fabulus. Near the hotel is Les Halles metro station which is a central station and it includes a forum . The location of the hotel allows you to walk to many famous buildings ehich is goodnif you want to wonder arround paris streets.

Nice and charming hotel. Very well located closed to the Louvre There are nice restaurants in the area.
The breakfast is excellent. Not many items but more than enough and all good quality. The rooms are clean and beautiful but very small. Not a real problem but something to take into account.

The hotel has a good location quite close to Louvre, plenty of cafes just around the corner, design is nice as well. Breakfast is "okay" but since you are in Paris it's better to have it in any of the vast variety of places nearby. Room service could have been better though.

It was a really nice stay in a cool boutique hotel with neat themed floors and an interesting design. While it would be small for a room in the US it's a great size in Paris and why would you spend much time inside in such a beautiful city?? It's totally worth the stay.

It was my boyfriend and I first trip to Paris and this hotel was unbelievably and surprisingly so nice! Man I wish I had photos, but I don't. I think I was too in the moment when I first arrived in Paris to take pics LOL Breakdown below:

ROOM - The room was so clean and cool! It's small with a small window but it was designed nicely. Felt like we were in a spaceship, but it wasn't tight at all. The lights from the room to the restroom made it look very upscale. Everything was modern and I have no complaints. I'd definitely recommend staying here if you want affordable, more than what you paid for, great service, and nice neighborhood.

STAFF - From the first day we walked in, the staff brought out a map and showed us all the great places to visit. We were shown all the metropolitan stations to take to get to certain destinations. The service was 24 hours and it was very comforting. Towards the end of our trip, we ran into a staff named Fabio. He was awesome! We weren't sure of what to do on our last day there, which was our 3rd day (short trip.. I know 😰), and he recommended us to take the Paris tour by boat. So, so glad we did. He also got us a taxi at 5am so we can ride back to the airport, something we didn't think of since we thought the bus was going to still be running 🙄 He basically took care of us.

After a long business trip of took a few days off to relax in Paris. Traveling solo made this boutique hotel with it's reasonable rates and good locations an easy pick. The hotel has a very, very helpful, kind, multilingual staff who helped me plan some day trips. On the downside, the lobby smelled of stale wine and the small rooms were not that well planned out. Small can be great if there are nooks and places to put your purse, water bottle etc, but there was hardly a surface to be had. I can't image how it would be with two people! But if you can live with that, the neighborhood is residential with lots of wonderful cafe's (the best food on my trip) and lovely patisseries with excellent coffee to sit and watch the local colour. And it's an easy walk to several Metro stations, as well at to the Louvre and more people watching along the Seine.

We enjoyed our stay at Hotel Odyssey. We were allowed to check in early, provided with lots of tips from the front desk and found the room comfortable and clean. It is a bit small, but that is to be expected in Europe especially in great locations.

Ok so this is a pretty cool hotel, the decor is very out there. The rooms are small but attractive which is fine if you are on your own but might be a tad annoying with two of you. What I didn't like was the wifi was awful which given I was there on business was really annoying. There is also a lack of coffee or a coffee machine in the hotel which was again very infuriating when you wake up and want to crack on with some work. The location is great with plenty of bars and restaurants nearby and the louvre is literally an 8 minute walk. So if you are going for a couples weekend it's probably going to be cool and funky but for business I would avoid.

Stayed at this hotel for a week - very clean and modern and a little bit quirky. The location was perfect with a 6 minute walk to the nearest metro and surrounded by lovely restaurants and bars. The room was perfect size for the two of us, and the bed was comfortable, and the air conditioning was a huge plus.. The hotel staff were extremely helpful and spoke very good english. The hotel also provide a mobile phone, which allows to make International calls and also to help use as a sat-nav around Paris, which was a huge help. The breakfast buffet was very tasty - but a little expensive.

Will definitely be visiting again - and would highly recommend to anyone who is looking for a hub to use to visit Paris.

Everything was amazing about this hotel, from location, staff, cleanliness to wifi speed. Only concern is if you're a big person, won't be able to use the bathroom. OK for small or average people though.

This hotel exceeded my expectations. Before arriving in Paris, I had heard how small the rooms were in all the hotels due to the nature of the buildings.
However, I was more than pleased with this hotel room. Yes the room was small, but it was perfect for our stay. We had a queen sized double bed, excellent shower, and toilet facilities. There was also a cupboard with a light inside it, and a shelf.

We were also given use of a mobile (cell) phone to use during our stay which was excellent. We used this to help plan our routes, call home and use the app for translating and the metro.

Wifi was also free which was great too (and very unusual these days) - huge selling point!
We stayed on the 5th floor, lift is small but effective. We used the stairs to go down most of the time.

We were about 5 minutes walk from the Louvre, and I also went a run on the Saturday morning (run routes are available from the hotel of 5k and 10k option) and took in some sites of Ile de St Louis, Notre Dame, Centre Pompidou and a run along the seine.

We were there for 2 nights, and I would most definitely return to this hotel and explore much more of the city.

Thank you to Maria who was always helpful and patient with our check in/out and help when we needed it.

Boutique hotel,. Not very spacious but clever design. Close to le Halles Metro and Marcel Etienne. Staff is super friendly as well and you are waljing distance from the Louvre. Great places to eat and drinm off etienne marcel with local crowds

Swift check in, lovely English speaking staff and then straight uo tp my cocoon room for a shower (great shower) Cocoon rooms are exactly what they are titled, your own little cocoon, air conditioned, versatile lighting, comfy bed, sound proofed walls, even the bedside table can be hidden in the wall to keep the natural minimalistic spaceship style of these rooms alive. Ideal for singles or couples wanting a hotel with a difference and your privacy. Brilliant for light travellers, small cupboard/ wardrobe with room safe inclusive. Keep your belongings tucked away in the small storage space to preserve the 'your bubble' effect. A welcome change from the run of the mill basic bedroom style hotels, highly recommended for those wanting something 'special' with a difference. If you like a cuppa in bed bring a travel kettle and some sachets or you'll have to pay 3.50€ per tiny cup from a vending machine. Breakfast is 16€ for a beautiful continental buffet spread, If you're in a rush you may find it better value for money to nip in a nearby cafe for a full hot breaky though. The breakfast lady Ma'te takes great pride in her breakfast spread it's an edible work of art, if paying for breakfast then all hot drinks are included. I'll be back at this little haven with my husband late October and maybe try an Odyssey room this time. This hotel will change your concept of hotels for the greater good. If there's a particular colour you don't like please state at time of booking. Can't wait to get back there, fantastic treat to chill out in a room with a difference after a hard days sightseeing then a wild night partying. ⛪
